Title: Ghostcatcher (EP)
Description:
Please note: product images are digital mockups. Actual products may vary in color, brand, style and/or production materials due to reasons beyond our control.

The 'Ghostcatcher' EP is named after the instrument, the Siberian Ghostcatcher. It is a mouthbow played by Shamans of the North to communicate with ghosts and insects, featured here on the track “Polaris”. The EP explores sublime energy spoken and unspoken, from the tranced out western desert bass grooves of “Joshua Tree”, to the indie roots folk story of a rambling woman in “Earth to Make Rain”, to the multi-hued kaleidoscopic world groove journey of “Polaris”, to the psychedelic African Ngoni supported cover of Black Sabbath’s “Planet Caravan”, featuring Emma Lucia on vocals

Release Date: October 28, 2022
Record Label: Swamptronic Records
Format + Color: Black

Tracklist:
A1 Joshua Tree
A2 Earth To Make Rain
B1 Polaris
B2 Planet Caravan
